Loaded Cornering

	Philosophy

		-
			In a debate, loaded cornering is the use of loaded questions to demand an absolute yes
			or no answer on a highly a highly complex complex and nuanced topic, the result being,
			because said topic is so nuanced that some non-zero case can be made in favor of the
			answer unfavorable answer to the opponent, that said unfavorable answer is implied to
			the audience.
